<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id83bac75b-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s1130"><num value="1130">§ 1130.</num><heading> Effect of division on other law</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This division does not impair or affect the authorities or responsibilities relating to the procurement of real property conferred by division C of this subtitle and chapters 1 to 11 of title 40.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id83bac75c-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/350/s3">Pub. L. 111–350, § 3</ref>, <date date="2011-01-04">Jan. 4, 2011</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3690">124 Stat. 3690</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
